The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Selectors to get   Rs 1 lakh
                                                                                                                       7                                      Selectors to get   Rs 1 lakh
            A STAFF REPORTER                            
	Calcutta: The CAB has decided the state senior selectors will receive an annual remuneration of Rs 1 lakh each from this year.         
	State senior selectors Sambaran Banerjee, Molay Banerjee, Devang Gandhi and Mintu Das will benefit by this move. It was, however, learnt that they are still not happy with the remuneration. An amount of Rs 1 lakh is meagre The CAB can afford to pay more, a selector said.         
	Meanwhile, the CAB selected Sujan Mukherjee as the joint secretary, at a special general body meeting.         
	According to sources, Debashish Ganguli, a South Suburban club official, has submitted a report with president Dalmiya, questioning Mukherjees selection.         
	The working committee is expected to meet on October 4. Two days later, the 25-member Bengal Ranji team is likely to be picked.                                                                                                                     
